Class Game<UI extends UserInterface>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Poker.components.Game<UI>
  • Type Parameters:
    UI - Type that extends the UserInterface interface which will be used for instantiating the i/o object

    public final class Game<UI extends UserInterface>
extends java.lang.Object
    The game instance All operation of the game and its logic are handled by this class. It accepts a generic type that extends the UserInterface interface which will be used for user input and output

      • nextRound

        public void nextRound()
        Executes all game mechanics that are required for the game to continue. At the end of the logical part of it the function also updates the game status using the interface specified by the user at the creation of the game session. There is no limit to how many sessions can be played in a game.

      • play

        public void play()
        Starts executing the game and stops when the user wants to quit The input is received by using the interface that has been selected at the creation of the game instance
